race.comment: ANTHRACIA (4) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start when ninth over 1000m at Gundagai. Maps well and all her wins have come at this track. LIAMENA AVENUE (6) was in the money over this journey two back, then failed at the longer trip last time when fourth at the Sapphire Coast. Well-placed and can bounce back. MARINE GIRL (9) resumes from a spell of three months and is having her first outing for Nick Olive. Finished eighth at Kempsey over 1250m at the opening run last time in work. Among the better hopes while fresh. CRUCIAL WITNESS (1) returned from a spell two weeks ago when sixth over 1000m at Canberra. Fitter and has a solid second-up record. Respect.
